reviewText: I have had this product in vhs form in past years when my (24 yr) old was growing and recently found it on DVD I have given it to my grandson and nephew for their birthday's and this product is still a HIT!!! It keeps their attention and makes smiles come to their faces. Thanks Amazon for the great selection of KIDS SONGS it keeps on giving through the years and makes little guys get up and moving Smiles, MOONSHINE GIRL
It's worth for the price of 2 bucks! compared to a brand new video tape.  Thank you for making my son explore his developing mind.:)
I love this video!!!! The sports theme creates a fun, exciting, energetic, video.  The songs are fun, and catchy.  Kids will LOVE this video!
great movie

I used these in my child care years ago and wanted my grandchildren to experience the positive messages instead of the garbage that is now on television.
My 21 month old loves it because he loves anything to do with sports...but the clothing is dated and I just was a little disappointed in the selection of songs.
We actually had this one when my children were young.  My daughters learned and performed cheers from this video. Thanks

Have loved these videos since my own children were young, now I buy them for the grand kids.  Some I keep at my house and some for them to use in the car.  The high activity level and live people action keeps their interest.
We bought this one because my son watched the other one so much, my husband couldn't repair it anymore! He loves KidSong Videos!
My son Dylan, 4, is a sports nut! He loves Kidsongs videos, so I knew this would be perfect for him! I wish it had more of the tv station part in it, but still a great video.

My toddler loves all these old kidsongs videos. This is my least favorite, because of the little girls in halter tops supposedly getting excited about the boy driving the race car. She's also not that interested in sports. All the other videos are dated, but good.
love it
Kidsongs dvd's are always good.
engaging, entertaining songs

My oldest granddaughter remembered these from her youth. She asked me about them on Easter, we began to sing the songs, her husband thought we had lost it!!! I told her to check Amazon I knew they would have them..... YEP! she ordered some, for her stepson, and I have too, You just need to sing these days, and what better way to SHARE with friends and family... If you have children, you will love" Kidsongs", and others too..  Thanks Amazon, my granddaughter is 23 now, .and she is still watching them....
It's cute and fun.  The one my kiddos enjoy the most is "What Do You Want To Be?"
My son loves this! He plays and sings with it daily!
